<TITLE> Ramesh promises permanent solution to Jamuna erosion </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj, Jan 8 (bdnews24.com)  The government will take long-term initiatives to prevent river erosion in Sirajganj and Bogra districts by Jamuna river, the water resources minister said on Thursday. "Rather than small and scattered initiatives in different areas to prevent river erosion, large projects will have to be taken to reach a permanent solution to the problem," Ramesh Chandra Sen. "The aim of our government is to save people," Ramesh told reporters at Bogra Circuit House, as he paused there in the noon on his way to his home district Thakurgaon. "And for that the government will remove complexities in the tender process of different projects of Water Development Board," he added. The Water Development Board Rajshahi zone chief engineer Sheikh Abdul Momin, Bogra deputy commissioner Md Humayun Kabir, police superintendent Akram Hossain, among others, were present at the Circuit House. Earlier in the morning, the minister, on his way, was greeted by Sirajganj Water Development Board executive engineer Md Nizamul Haq Bhuiyan in Sirajganj. Sen said two good news were waiting for farmers in next two weeksa cut in diesel prices and the open-market sale of fertilisers. On Wednesday, the first meeting of Sheikh Hasina's new cabinet had decided to increase fertiliser subsidies and cut diesel prices. The meeting also decided to revive the fertiliser distribution method followed during the 1996-2001 Awami League administration. bdnews24.co
